'''
Strings in python:
------------------

name = 'charan'
name = "charan"

Multiline String:
Three single quotes or three double quotes
(''' ''')
(""" """)


len() - By using len() function we can know how many characters are present in side a string.
message = "Veeranki sai charan"
print(len(message)) #OutPut: 19
Changing the case of a string:
------------------------------
upper() - it convers the entire string into upper chase letters

message = "Veeranki Sai Charan"
capital_text = message.upper()
print(capital_text) #Output: VEERANKI SAI CHARAN

lower() - it converts the entire string into lower case letters.

message = "VEERANKI SAI CHARAN"
lower_string = message.lower()
print(lower_string) #veeranki sai charan

Finding sub string in a string:
-------------------------------
find() - The fing method returns the index value where the substring starts or -1 if its not found
the in keyword checks weather the substring is present in the string or not it present it returns True else False

text  = "My name is sai charan and i am from vijayawada"
print(text.find(vijayawada)) #output: 36
print("vijayawada" in text) #Output: True


replace() - this replace method replaces all the instances with the given name.

split() - Converts string to list based on specified delimeter.
By default the space is taken as a delimeter.

text = "Banana, apple, cherry"
split_text = text.split(",")
print(split_text)

join() - it will covert list to string.
join_text = " - ".join(split_text)
print(join_text)

''' 